<item>
            <title>[SPR-2903] Offer basic distribution that includes javadoc</title>
                <link>https://jira.spring.io/browse/SPR-2903</link>
                <project id="10000" key="SPR">Spring Framework</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The standard distribution (spring-framework-2.0.1.zip) does not include API javadocs.  There are no downloads in the documentation page either.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
            <key id="15613">SPR-2903</key>
            <summary>Offer basic distribution that includes javadoc</summary>
                <type id="2" iconUrl="https://jira.spring.io/images/icons/issuetypes/newfeature.png">New Feature</type>
                                            <priority id="4" iconUrl="https://jira.spring.io/images/icons/priorities/minor.png">Minor</priority>
                        <status id="6" iconUrl="https://jira.spring.io/images/icons/statuses/closed.png" description="The issue is considered finished, the resolution is correct. Issues which are not closed can be reopened.">Closed</status>
                    <statusCategory id="3" key="done" colorName="green"/>
                                    <resolution id="1">Fixed</resolution>
                                        <assignee username="juergen.hoeller">Juergen Hoeller</assignee>
                                    <reporter username="rogeriomgatto">Rog&#233;rio Meneguelli Gatto</reporter>
                        <labels>
                    </labels>
                <created>Fri, 1 Dec 2006 04:05:02 +0000</created>
                <updated>Tue, 19 Jun 2012 03:50:25 +0000</updated>
                            <resolved>Tue, 9 Oct 2007 04:04:32 +0000</resolved>
                                    <version>2.0.1</version>
                                    <fixVersion>2.5 RC1</fixVersion>
                                        <due></due>
                            <votes>0</votes>
                                    <watches>1</watches>
                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="21161" author="juergen.hoeller" created="Fri, 1 Dec 2006 10:09:07 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This is deliberate as of Spring 2.0: The javadocs are quite large, hence the standard distribution does not include them anymore. The only way to download the javadoc is as part of the -with-dependencies distribution.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I take this as a request for a distribution that includes the contents of the standard distro as well as the javadoc, similar to the Spring 1.2 standard distribution. We could offer this as a third zip file: e.g. spring-framework-2.1-with-docs.zip, if there is enough demand for it (that cannot be satisfied with the larger -with-dependencies distro).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Juergen&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="21205" author="rogeriomgatto" created="Tue, 5 Dec 2006 05:10:27 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hummm, I understand.  I wasn&apos;t aware that the -with-dependencies distribution contained the javadocs.  I like the idea of a third distribution for the following reasons:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;I can&apos;t really configure spring without knowledge of which beans, interceptors, properties etc. are available.  It&apos;s very convenient to have this information local in addition to an online version.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The -with-dependencies distribution is too large, and brings many (usually) unecessary libs, even if I&apos;ll use them anyway.  For instance, I&apos;ll download hibernate anyway for the documentation, so I don&apos;t need it with my spring download.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;Thanks for the quick evaluation.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="21238" author="al0" created="Wed, 6 Dec 2006 20:53:04 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Probably docs-only distribution?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="22636" author="asenft" created="Thu, 8 Mar 2007 19:11:18 +0000"  >
&lt;p&gt;I would also prefer a &quot;docs only&quot; distribution. This approach is also taken on various other projects where the docs are a separate download.&lt;br/&gt;
Providing permutations of the distro seems a bit awkward to me.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Just my opinion,&lt;br/&gt;
Andreas&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="25135" author="paul4christ79" created="Wed, 1 Aug 2007 09:30:19 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Agreed. A docs only distribution is preferred.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="26816" author="juergen.hoeller" created="Tue, 9 Oct 2007 04:04:32 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I eventually decided to go with a spring-framework-with-docs.zip distribution, including not only all documentation but also all source jars (even for the modules) as well as the source for the samples. Such an intermediate distribution seems to be a very nice option, with a size of ~32 MB.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Since we have that with-docs distribution now, I&apos;ve reduced spring-framework.zip to the minimal binaries: no doc PDF and no global source zip there anymore. This minimal distribution has a size of 5.5 MB now, which is a nice option as well.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I don&apos;t see further permutations coming, since those three options seem to cover all relevant audiences now: 1. binary only; 2. binary plus sources/documentation/samples; 3. everything you need to build the framework yourself.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Juergen&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
